    "body": "Better idea. Write some network characteristics into the DB (or metadata) such as the contract address, genesis fork version, and check these data on start up. Refuse to start (with a nice message!) if they do not match.\r\n\r\nThis is better since it can be made backward compatible (just skip the check if the data is not present). Also, it does not need to apply only to the default DB, or to nodes started with `--network==`.\r\n\r\nProbably doesn't apply so well for log files, but they are not so critical.",
